    {
      "id": "1ad4750c-f3ba-80dc-987c-d7c5c1f7bba3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This study measures the degree to which student perception of the time they need to spend on a course actually maps to the credit hours expected for a specific course. Authors compare whether credit hours explain student effort (don’t seem to), as the number of deliverables student need to do actually is a much better predictor. Authors argue for the adoption of a new construct of course load than credit hours. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1ad4750c-f3ba-80dc-987c-d7c5c1f7bba3",
        "parent": {
